  "label": {
    "en": [
      "KW 129 C 3 (TEST — duplicate labels & duplicate images)"
    ]
  },
  "summary": {
    "en": [
      "SYNTHETIC TEST MANIFEST. Exercises three collision types: (1) duplicate canvas LABELS (same label -> same derived Commons filename): images 1,2,3 and 5,7. (2) duplicate IMAGES within the manifest (identical URL -> identical SHA-1): images 4=8 and 9=10. (3) images that ALREADY EXIST on Commons byte-for-byte (SHA-1 match -> exists-on-commons flag at import): image 11 = File:Karel van de Woestijne, 1904 - BBB-1560.jpg (sha1 884664f4...), image 12 = File:World map ... J.F. Martinet\".jpg (sha1 6a249cf8...). Bodies 1-10 point at a real KB manifest; 11-12 at the Commons originals (upload.wikimedia.org, CORS *). Self-hosted on GitHub raw (CORS-open) so it loads by URL."
    ]
  },
